{
  "text": "Beamwalk analysis, used to measure balance and motor function, showed that mice injected with ␣-synuclein lentivirus performed worse than mice injected with control virus (Fig. 8) , confirming previous studies that lentiviral overexpression of ␣-synuclein in the substantia nigra produces a dysfunction of motor performance [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . A comparison of the effects of various ␣-synuclein mutants with WT ␣-synuclein revealed that exactly those mutations that increased ␣-synuclein aggregation (Fig. 7) also increased the motor impairment upon nigrostriatal expression (Fig. 8) . The only difference between the aggregation and motor dysfunction effects of ␣-synuclein mutants was that the deletion of the N-terminal 8 residues did not decrease the increased aggregation of C-terminally truncated ␣-synuclein (Fig.  7) , but did prevent the enhancement of motor dysfunction induced by the C-terminal truncation (Fig. 8) .",
  "correct_citation": {
